What you need to know:

The NSE-20—which tracks the 20 best performing counters— gained 6.2 percent in that month from November while all share index points also rose by 4.8 percent.Bamburi cement also gained 5.4 percent month-on-month to close at Sh37.85 as NCBA and DTB rose by 18.9 percent and 21.5 percent respectively in the same period.Safaricom in particular touched a new-all-time high of Sh36.50, sending excitement to the market, especially with foreign investors turning net buyers.